Comment: The other day, I couldn't resist having a peak through my buddy, The Dentist's past games profile because his rating had suddenly shot up about 18 points.  I saw this brevity and I couldn't help playing through it to see how The Dentist managed to pulverise his opponent in just TWELVE MOVES!  I saw how, he showed his opponent the utter folly of leaving the Fool's Mate diagonal unprotected.  Yes, white was certainly awakened from a Fool's Paradise.

3. f5? - bad move - this leaves the Fool's Mate diagonal unprotected to the BQ.  Better was Nf3 guarding the h4 square and developing a piece at the same time - in this case white will now drop a pawn as 3........ Qh4  forks WK and e4 pawn.

4. ........ Qxe4  - after 4. g3?? this allows another queen fork on e4 and the WR on h1 is toast.  The Dentist may have a low rating, but as you saw with my earlier annotated game "In the Dentist's Chair" in which I very nearly lost he is not to be underestimated!  Now white really feels the drill as a lot of enammel is about to disappear from his side of the board!!
